headline: Carnival Corporation & plc Announces Closing of $1.0 Billion 5.875% Senior Unsecured Notes Offering for Refinancing and Interest Expense Reduction
summary: Carnival Corporation & plc (NYSE/LSE: CCL; NYSE: CUK) today announced that Carnival Corporation (the "Company") has closed its previously announced private offering (the "Notes Offering") of $1.0 billion aggregate principal amount of 5.875% senior unsecured notes due 2031 (the "Notes"). The Company will use the net proceeds from the Notes Offering to redeem the Company's $993 million 7.625% senior unsecured notes due 2026 (the "2026 Unsecured Notes"). headline: 3 Promising Growth Stocks You Can Buy for Less Than $100

At less than $100 per share, here's why these can be good growth stocks to load up on today.
